# Tool Definitions

Tools follow the Vercel AI SDK pattern:

```typescript
tools.cl_example = tool({
  description: "MUTABLE - Description of what this tool does.",
  inputSchema: z.object({
    resource_type: z.string().describe("Resource type (e.g. orders)"),
  }),
  execute: async ({ resource_type }) => {
    const ctx = await fetchResourceContext(account, resource_type, id);
    await requireConfirm(confirmFn, "cl_example", { resource_type }, ctx);
    // ... API call ...
  },
});
```

## Naming conventions

- Read-only: `cl_list_`, `cl_get_`, `cl_search_` — no confirmation needed
- Mutations: action verb (`cl_cancel_`, `cl_update_`, `cl_delete_`, `cl_create_`, `cl_ship_`)
- All mutations MUST call `requireConfirm(confirmFn, toolName, args, context?)` before executing
- Mutation detection: `MUTATION_PREFIXES` array in `cl-tools.ts` and `MUTATION_KEYWORDS` regex in `mcp-tools.ts`

## API integration

- `clFetch(account, path, options)` — OAuth tokens cached with 60s expiry buffer, auto-retry on 429/5xx
- Filtering: ransack-style syntax (`_eq`, `_cont` suffixes)
- Pagination: `page_size` 1–25, `page_number`, default sort `-created_at`
- `formatResource()` / `formatList()` format JSON:API responses for display
